  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced in House",
    "asOf": "2020-07-16",
    "date": "2020-10-29T14:01:40Z",
    "text": "COVID-19 Student Loan Relief Act (CSLRA) of 2020 \n\nThis bill allows student loan debt to be discharged in bankruptcy if (1) the debtor's income has declined by a specified amount during the COVID-19 (i.e., coronavirus disease 2019) outbreak or as a result of the outbreak, or (2) the primary income earner of the debtor's family died or became seriously disabled as a result of COVID-19."
